</para><para id="eip-173"><media id="oedkimpulse" alt="echoimpulse">
      <audio mime-type="audio/x-wav" src="HighReverbImpulse.wav"/>
   </media> The same impulse played in Heavily Echoic Room. The difference in reverberation time is audible.</para></example><para id="import-auto-id1167263460453">Reverberation time is a good way to diagnose how badly a room echoes a generated signal. The actual echo cancellation process involves digitally filtering out the decaying copies of the generated speech signals that cause the room’s poor reverberation times. </para>
